Two people have been killed in the Mowe-Ofada area of Ogun State in a renewed fight between two cult groups. A fight broke out in the state following a fresh crisis which reportedly started late on Thursday and continued until Friday morning. It was gathered that the cri­sis was sparked off by a clash between two opposing cult as­sociations. -Advertisement- According to an eyewit­ness, a member of the cult was reportedly killed at Ofada on Thursday evening. A reprisal attack from the opposition cult led to the gruesome death of another young man whose life­less body was sighted around Aje-Onibode area around Mowe on Friday morning. This caused fear among residents as most shops were not open for business until noon on Friday. The Ogun State Police Pub­lic Relations Officer, Abimbola Oyeyemi, while confirming the incident said the clash was between two rival cult groups. “It is a fight between two ri­val groups. One of the cultists was killed yesterday (Thurs­day) but the situation has been brought under control “We have arrested a suspect in relation to the violence,” Oy­eyemi said. Also in Lagos State, a clash took place on Friday around Iyana Ipaja area of Lagos. POLL According to an eyewitness, the clash was as a result of Thursday’s clash between two cult gangs in Lagos. He said armed riot policemen had been drafted to the place.